                 EPA
                
            
            
            Image caption
                
                    Thousands of Americans have visited the Capitol Rotunda to pay their respects
                
            The Prince of Wales, German Chancellor Angela Merkel, and Jordan's King Abdullah II are among the world figures there to pay their respects.Former leaders, including John Major, who was UK prime minister for most of Mr Bush's term, will also attend.A life in pictures
Service dog Sully pays touching last tribute
Wednesday has been declared a national day of mourning - many government offices, and US stock exchanges, will be closed.
